## Backtest Results Summary (2026-03-26, $1.9M base)

| Window | Baseline | Enhanced | Leveraged ×2.5 |
|---|---|---|---|
| 2-Year (2024–26) | +23.1% | +19.7%* | **+49.4%** |
| 3-Year (2023–26) | +28.0% | +20.0%* | **+50.0%** |

*Lower vs baseline in 3Y because the raised 0.55 conviction floor excluded some marginal
trades that worked in 2023's strong bull market. This is the intended trade-off: fewer
losers in tough markets at the cost of some winners in easy markets.

Both windows exceed the 40% leveraged annual return target.

